1 (a) (1) Subject to subsection (c) of this section, the Department shall make a
2 site visit and conduct a full survey of each licensed nursing home at least once per calendar
3 year.
4 (2) Unless otherwise required by federal law, all surveys shall be
5 unannounced.
6 (b) (1) Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Department shall
7 initiate an investigation of a nursing home complaint alleging actual harm within 10
8 business days after receiving the complaint.
9 (2) If the Department receives a complaint against a nursing home alleging
10 immediate jeopardy to a resident, the Department:
11 (i) Shall make every effort to investigate the complaint within 24
12 hours after receiving the complaint; and
13 (ii) Shall investigate the complaint not later than 48 hours after
14 receiving the complaint.
15 (c) If ownership of a licensed nursing home is transferred to a person that does
16 not own or operate another nursing home in the State at the time of the transfer, the
17 Department shall conduct:
18 (1) The first full survey of the licensed nursing home as required under
19 subsection (a) of this section within 3 months after the date of transfer; and
20 (2) An unannounced, on–site follow–up survey of the licensed nursing
21 home that covers any deficiencies noted in the full survey within 120 days after the full
22 survey was completed.
23 (D) (1) ON REQUEST OF A COUNTY, THE SECRETARY SHALL DELEGATE TO
24 THE COUNTY THE AUTHORITY TO CONDUCT SITE VISITS AND FULL SURVEYS AND
25 COMPLAINT INVESTIGATIONS OF NURSING HOMES AUTHORIZED UNDER THIS
26 SECTION.
27 (2) (I) WITHIN 90 DAYS AFTER RECEIVING A REQUEST FROM A
28 COUNTY, THE SECRETARY SHALL EXECUTE A MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING
29 WITH THE COUNTY TO DELEGATE THE AUTHORITY TO CONDUCT SURVEYS AND
30 COMPLAINT INVESTIGATIONS OF NURSING HOMES AUTHORIZED UNDER THIS
31 SECTION.
32 (II) THE MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING SHALL BE
33 MODELED ON THE MARYLAND DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH STANDARD
34 MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING INTRA–AGENCY/INTERGOVERNMENTAL

SENATE BILL 376 3
1 AGREEMENT, ENTITLED NURSING HOME FACILITIES, THAT EXISTED BETWEEN THE
2 DEPARTMENT AND MONTGOMERY COUNTY ON JULY 1, 2019.
3 (2) (3) THE DEPARTMENT AND THE COUNTY SHALL EQUALLY
4 SHARE THE COSTS OF CONDUCTING SITE VISITS AND FULL SURVEYS DELEGATED BY
5 THE SECRETARY UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
6 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
7 October July 1, 2025.
